February 24, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REORGANIZE CHAPTER 115D OF THE GENERAL STATUTES AND MAKE
3 NECESSARY CONFORMING CHANGES.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5
6 PART I. REORGANIZATION OF CHAPTER 115D
7 SECTION 1.(a) Article 1 of Chapter 115D of the General Statutes reads as rewritten:
8 "Article 1.
9 "General Provisions for State Administration.
10 "Part 1. Establishment and Administration of the North Carolina Community Colleges System.
11 "§ 115D-1. Statement of purpose.
12 The purposes of this Chapter are to provide for the establishment, organization, and
13 administration of a system of educational institutions throughout the State offering courses of
14 instruction in one or more of the general areas of two-year college parallel, technical, vocational,
15 and adult education programs, to serve as a legislative charter for such institutions, and to
16 authorize the levying of local taxes and the issuing of local bonds for the support thereof. The
17 major purpose of each and every institution operating under the provisions of this Chapter shall
18 be and shall continue to be the offering of vocational and technical education and training, and
19 of basic, high school level, academic education needed in order to profit from vocational and
20 technical education, for students who are high school graduates or who are beyond the
21 compulsory age limit of the public school system and who have left the public schools, provided,
22 juveniles of any age committed to the Division of Juvenile Justice of the Department of Public
23 Safety by a court of competent jurisdiction may, if approved by the director of the youth
24 development center to which they are assigned, take courses offered by institutions of the system
25 if they are otherwise qualified for admission.
26 The Community Colleges System Office is designated as the primary lead agency for
27 delivering workforce development training, adult literacy training, and adult education programs
28 in the State.
29 …
30 "§ 115D-1.3. Accreditation of secondary school located in North Carolina shall not be a
31 factor in admissions, loans, scholarships, or other educational policies.
32 (a) For purposes of this section, the term "accreditation" shall include certification or any
33 other similar approval process.
34 (b) The State Board of Community Colleges shall adopt a policy that prohibits any
35 community college from soliciting or using information regarding the accreditation of a
36 secondary school located in North Carolina that a person attended as a factor affecting
