1 institutions as the State Board may deem necessary to insure the quality of educational programs,
2 to promote the systematic meeting of educational needs of the State, and to provide for the
3 equitable distribution of State and federal funds to the several institutions.
4 The State Board of Community Colleges shall establish standards and scales for salaries and
5 allotments paid from funds administered by the State Board, and all employees of the institutions
6 shall be exempt from the provisions of the North Carolina Human Resources Act. Any and all
7 salary caps set by the State Board for community college presidents shall apply only to the
8 State-paid portion of the salary. Except as otherwise provided by law, the employer contribution
9 rate on the local-paid portion of the salary, to be paid from local funds, shall be set by the State
10 Treasurer based on actuarial recommendations. The State Board shall have authority with respect
11 to individual institutions: to approve sites, capital improvement projects, budgets; to approve the
12 selection of the chief administrative officer; to establish and administer standards for professional
13 personnel, curricula, admissions, and graduation; to regulate the awarding of degrees, diplomas,
14 and certificates; to establish and regulate student tuition and fees within policies for tuition and
15 fees established by the General Assembly; and to establish and regulate financial accounting
16 procedures.
17 The State Board of Community Colleges shall require each community college to meet the
18 faculty credential requirements of its accrediting agency for all community college programs.
19 (a1) Notwithstanding G.S. 66-58(c)(3) or any other provisions of law, the State Board of
20 Community Colleges may adopt rules governing the expenditure of funds derived from bookstore
21 sales by community colleges. These expenditures shall be consistent with the mission and
22 purpose of the Community College System. Profits may be used in the support and enhancement
23 of the bookstores, for student aid or scholarships, for expenditures of direct benefit to students,
24 and for other similar expenditures authorized by the board of trustees, subject to rules adopted
25 by the State Board. These funds shall not be used to supplement salaries of any personnel.
26 (a2) The State Board of Community Colleges shall comply with the provisions of
27 G.S. 116-11(10a) to plan and implement an exchange of information between the public schools
28 and the institutions of higher education in the State.
29 (a3) The State Board of Community Colleges shall adopt the following rules to assist
30 community colleges in their administration of procedures necessary to implement G.S. 20-11 and
31 G.S. 20-13.2:
32 (1) To establish the procedures a person who is or was enrolled in a community
33 college must follow and the requirements that person must meet to obtain a
34 driving eligibility certificate.
35 (2) To require the person who is required under G.S. 20-11(n) to sign the driving
36 eligibility certificate to provide the certificate if he or she determines that one
37 of the following requirements is met:
38 a. The person seeking the certificate is eligible for the certificate under
39 G.S. 20-11(n)(1) and is not subject to G.S. 20-11(n1).
40 b. The person seeking the certificate is eligible for the certificate under
41 G.S. 20-11(n)(1) and G.S. 20-11(n1).
42 (3) To provide for an appeal through the grievance procedures established by the
43 board of trustees of each community college by a person who is denied a
44 driving eligibility certificate.
45 (4) To define exemplary student behavior and to define what constitutes the
46 successful completion of a drug or alcohol treatment counseling program.
47 The State Board also shall develop policies as to when it is appropriate to
48 notify the Division of Motor Vehicles that a person who is or was enrolled in
49 a community college no longer meets the requirements for a driving eligibility
50 certificate. The State Board also shall adopt guidelines to assist the presidents
