27 "§ 115D-9.15. Lease purchase and installment purchase contracts.
28 The State Board of Community Colleges shall review and approve lease purchase and
29 installment purchase contracts as provided under G.S. 115D-58.15(b). The State Board shall
30 adopt policies and procedures governing the review and approval process.
31 "§ 115D-9.20. Compliance review and requested information.
32 (a) Compliance Review. – The State Board of Community Colleges shall maintain an
33 accountability function that conducts periodic reviews of each community college operating
34 under the provisions of this Chapter. The purpose of the compliance review shall be to ensure
35 that (i) data used to allocate State funds among community colleges is reported accurately to the
36 System Office and (ii) community colleges are charging and waiving tuition and registration fees
37 consistent with law. The State Board of Community Colleges shall require the use of a
38 statistically valid sample size in performing compliance reviews of community colleges. All
39 compliance review findings that are determined to be material shall be forwarded to the college
40 president, local college board of trustees, the State Board of Community Colleges, and the State
41 Auditor. The State Board of Community Colleges shall adopt rules governing the frequency,
42 scope, and standard of materiality for compliance reviews.
43 (b) Information to Department of Revenue. – The North Carolina Community Colleges
44 System Office shall provide the Department of Revenue with a list of all community colleges,
45 including name, address, and other identifying information requested by the Department of
46 Revenue. The North Carolina Community Colleges System Office shall update this list whenever
47 there is a change.
48 "§ 115D-9.25. Multicampus centers.
49 All multicampus centers approved by the State Board of Community Colleges shall receive
50 funding under the same formula. The State Board of Community Colleges shall not approve any
51 additional multicampus centers without identified recurring sources of funding. A community
Senate Bill 125-First Edition Page 13

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 college facility shall be considered a multicampus center if it meets the criteria established by the
2 State Board and is at least 4 miles away from the main campus of the community college and
3 other multicampus center locations.
4 "§ 115D-9.30. Service areas.
5 The State Board of Community Colleges shall review, at least every five years, service areas
6 that include counties assigned to more than one community college to determine the feasibility
7 of continuing to assign those counties to more than one community college. The State Board
8 shall revise service areas as needed to ensure that counties are served effectively. The State Board
9 shall report its findings and any revisions to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee
10 within 60 days of revisions being made.
11 "§ 115D-9.35. Athletic teams.
12 The State Board of Community Colleges shall monitor community colleges for compliance
13 with Article 38 of Chapter 116 of the General Statutes. If the State Board determines that a
14 community college is in violation of Article 38 of Chapter 116 of the General Statutes, it shall
15 report the identity of the community college to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight
16 Committee.
