18 "Part 3. Community College Programs.
19 "§ 115D-10.5. Program funding.
20 (a) New Programs and Terminations of Programs. – A community college may not offer
21 a new program without the approval of the State Board of Community Colleges except that
22 approval shall not be required if the tuition for the program will fully cover the cost of the
23 program. If at any time tuition fails to fully cover the cost of a program that falls under the
24 exception, the program shall be discontinued unless approved by the State Board. If a proposed
25 new program would serve more than one community college, the State Board shall perform a
26 feasibility study prior to acting on the proposal. The State Board shall consider whether a regional
27 approach can be used when developing new programs and, to the extent possible, shall initiate
28 new programs on a regional basis. The State Board shall collect data on an annual basis on all
29 new programs and program terminations it approved and any regionalization of programs during
30 the year, including the specific reasons for which each program was terminated or approved.
31 (b) Recreation Extension Courses. – Funds appropriated to the Community Colleges
32 System Office as operating expenses for allocation to the institutions comprising the North
33 Carolina Community College System shall not be used to support recreation extension courses.
34 The financing of these courses by any institution shall be on a self-supporting basis, and
35 membership hours produced from these activities shall not be counted when computing full-time
36 equivalent students (FTE) for use in budget-funding formulas at the State level.
37 (c) Real Estate Continuing Education Courses. – Whenever a community college offers
38 real estate continuing education courses, the courses shall be offered on a self-supporting basis.
39 "§ 115D-10.10. College transfer program approval; standards for programs; annual
40 reporting requirements.
41 (a) The State Board of Community Colleges may approve the addition of the college
42 transfer program to a community college. If addition of the college transfer program to an
43 institution would require a substantial increase in funds, State Board approval shall be subject to
44 appropriation of funds by the General Assembly for this purpose.
45 (b) Addition of the college transfer program shall not decrease an institution's ability to
46 provide programs within its basic mission of vocational and technical training and basic academic
47 education.
48 (c) The State Board of Community Colleges shall develop appropriate criteria and
49 standards to regulate the addition of the college transfer program to institutions.
50 (d) The State Board of Community Colleges shall develop appropriate criteria and
51 standards to regulate the operation of college transfer programs.
