24 SECTION 1.(e) Article 2 of Chapter 115D of the General Statutes is amended by
25 adding a new section to read:
26 "§ 115D-21.10. Curriculum courses taught throughout year.
27 Community colleges may teach curriculum courses at any time during the year, including the
28 summer term. Student membership hours from these courses shall be counted when computing
29 full-time equivalent students (FTE) for use in budget funding formulas at the State level."
