20 "§ 115D-30.5. Evaluation of Career and College Promise Program.
21 (a) Evaluation. – In addition to the evaluation of cooperative innovative high schools by
22 the State Board of Education pursuant to G.S. 115C-238.55, the State Board of Community
23 Colleges, in conjunction with the State Board of Education and the Board of Governors of The
24 University of North Carolina, shall evaluate the success of students participating in the Career
25 and College Promise Program, including the College Transfer pathway and the Career and
26 Technical Education pathway.
27 (b) Metrics. – Success shall be measured by high school retention rates, high school
28 completion rates, high school dropout rates, certification and associate degree completion,
29 admission to four-year institutions, postgraduation employment in career or study-related fields,
30 and employer satisfaction of employees who participated in the programs. The evaluation shall
31 also include an analysis of the cost of students participating in each of the programs within the
32 Career and College Promise Program, including at least the following:
33 (1) Total enrollment funding, the number of budgeted full-time equivalent
34 students, and the number of students enrolled in courses through cooperative
35 innovative high schools, the College Transfer pathway, and the Career and
36 Technical Education pathway.
37 (2) The cost and number of waivers of tuition and registration fees provided for
38 students enrolled in courses through cooperative innovative high schools, the
39 College Transfer pathway, and the Career and Technical Education pathway.
40 (3) Any additional costs of a student attending courses on campus if a student is
41 not attending public school in a local school administrative unit for the
42 majority of the student's instructional time.
43 (c) Report. – The Boards shall jointly report by March 15 of each year to the Joint
44 Legislative Education Oversight Committee, the Senate Appropriations Committee on
45 Education/Higher Education, the House Appropriations Committee on Education, and the Fiscal
46 Research Division of the General Assembly. The report shall be combined with the evaluation
47 of cooperative innovative high schools required by G.S. 115C-238.55, and the Community
48 Colleges System Office shall be responsible for submitting the combined report.
