11 in which the person is enrolled.
12 Notwithstanding any other law, the decision concerning whether a driving eligibility
13 certificate was properly issued or improperly denied shall be appealed only as provided under
14 the rules adopted in accordance with G.S. 115C-12(28), 115D-5(a3), 115D-10.70, or 115C-566,
15 whichever is applicable, and may not be appealed under this Chapter."
16 SECTION 2.(b) G.S. 20-13.2(c1) reads as rewritten:
17 "(c1) Upon receipt of notification from the proper school authority that a person no longer
18 meets the requirements for a driving eligibility certificate under G.S. 20-11(n), the Division must
19 expeditiously notify the person that his or her permit or license is revoked effective on the
20 thirtieth calendar day after the mailing of the revocation notice. The Division must revoke the
21 permit or license of that person on the thirtieth calendar day after the mailing of the revocation
22 notice. Notwithstanding subsection (d) of this section, the length of revocation must last for the
23 following periods:
24 (1) If the revocation is because of ineligibility for a driving eligibility certificate
25 under G.S. 20-11(n)(1), then the revocation shall last until the person's
26 eighteenth birthday.
27 (2) If the revocation is because of ineligibility for a driving eligibility certificate
28 under G.S. 20-11(n1), then the revocation shall be for a period of one year.
29 For a person whose permit or license was revoked due to ineligibility for a driving eligibility
30 certificate under G.S. 20-11(n)(1), the Division must restore a person's permit or license before
31 the person's eighteenth birthday, if the person submits to the Division one of the following:
32 (1) A high school diploma or its equivalent.
33 (2) A driving eligibility certificate as required under G.S. 20-11(n).
34 If the Division restores a permit or license that was revoked due to ineligibility for a driving
35 eligibility certificate under G.S. 20-11(n)(1), any record of revocation or suspension shall be
36 expunged by the Division from the person's driving record. The Division shall not expunge a
37 suspension or revocation record if a person has had a prior expunction from the person's driving
38 record for any reason.
39 For a person whose permit or license was revoked due to ineligibility for a driving eligibility
40 certificate under G.S. 20-11(n1), the Division shall restore a person's permit or license before the
41 end of the revocation period, if the person submits to the Division a driving eligibility certificate
42 as required under G.S. 20-11(n).
43 Notwithstanding any other law, the decision concerning whether a driving eligibility
44 certificate was properly issued or improperly denied shall be appealed only as provided under
45 the rules adopted in accordance with G.S. 115C-12(28), 115D-5(a3), 115D-10.70, or 115C-566,
46 whichever is applicable, and may not be appealed under this Chapter."
